revision.text:
The '''78th Independent Infantry Regiment''' was a military formation of the [[Korean People's Army]] during the 20th Century.

Along with the [[25th Infantry Brigade (North Korea)|25th Infantry Brigade]], it defended both the military and topographic crests leading from Inchon to Seoul after the [[Battle of Inchon|Inchon]] landing.<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/kw-unoff/unoff.htm |title=The Korean War: The UN Offensive |first=Stephen L.Y. |last=Gammons |id=CMH Pub 19-7 |publisher=[[United States Army Center of Military History]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100612073352/http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/kw-unoff/unoff.htm |archivedate=2010-06-12 }}</ref>

