'''Baga Sola''' ({{lang-ar|باغا سولا}}) is a town on the shore of [[Lake Chad]] in western [[Chad]].<ref name="bbclakechadsbagasolatownhit">{{cite news|title=Lake Chad's Baga Sola town hit by suicide bombers|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34498417|accessdate=February 25, 2017|work=BBC|date=October 10, 2015}}</ref><ref name="lacroixfrappeautchadeta">{{cite news|title=Boko Haram frappe au Tchad et au Cameroun|url=http://www.la-croix.com/Actualite/Monde/Afrique/Boko-Haram-frappe-au-Tchad-et-au-Cameroun-2015-10-11-1367230|accessdate=February 25, 2017|work=La Croix|date=October 11, 2015}}</ref> It has a hospital and a fish market,<ref name="bbclakechadsbagasolatownhit"/> and a refugee camp for Nigerians and Chadians who fled [[Boko Haram]].<ref name="lacroixfrappeautchadeta"/> 

Baga Sola was attacked by Boko Haram suicide bombers on October 10, 2015.<ref name="bbclakechadsbagasolatownhit"/> 41 people were killed in the attack.<ref name="lacroixfrappeautchadeta"/>

