{{Infobox magazine | title = Cuvânt moldovenesc | image_file = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = [[Nicolae Alexandri]] | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = [[Pan Halippa]], [[Simion Murafa]], [[Simion Murafa]], [[Ion Pelivan]], [[Mihail Ciachir]], [[Gheorghe Stîrcea]], [[T. Inculeţ]] | frequency = | circulation = | category = Politics, History | company = | publisher = | founded = 1913 | firstdate = | finaldate = 1917 | country = [[Bessarabia]] | based = [[Chișinău]] | language = [[Romanian language|Romanian]] | website = | issn = }}
'''''Cuvânt moldovenesc''''' ({{lang-en|Moldovan Word}}) was a magazine from [[Chișinău]], [[Bessarabia]], founded in 1913.<ref>[http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf PRESA BASARABEANĂ de la începuturi pînă în anul 1957. Catalog] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035846/http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf |date=March 4, 2012 }}</ref>
== History == The [[editor in chief]] was [[Nicolae Alexandri]], redactors were [[Pan Halippa]] and [[Simion Murafa]], and among the authors were: [[Ion Pelivan]], [[Daniel Ciugureanu]], [[Mihail Ciachir]], [[Gheorghe Stârcea]], [[T. Inculeţ]]. After May 1917, its successor was [[Școala Moldovenească]] of [[Onisifor Ghibu]].<ref>[http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf PRESA BASARABEANĂ de la începuturi pînă în anul 1957. Catalog] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035846/http://www.hasdeu.md/ro/ebibl/poslednij.pdf |date=March 4, 2012 }}</ref>
