{{Infobox flag | Name = Republika Srpska | Image = Flag of Republika Srpska.svg | Proportion = 1:2 | Adoption = {{start date and age|1992|11|24|df=y}} | Design = [[Tricolor (flag)|Tricolour]], made of three equal horizontal bands of [[red]], [[blue]] and [[white]]. }}
The '''flag of [[Republika Srpska]]''' was adopted on 24 November 1992<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://zeljko-heimer-fame.from.hr/descr/ba-rs.html|title=The FAME: Republic of Srpska|last=Heimer|first=Zeljko|website=zeljko-heimer-fame.from.hr|access-date=2018-03-18}}</ref>. The flag is a rectangular [[tricolor (flag)|tricolour]] with three equal horizontal bands of red, blue and white.<ref>[http://www.crwflags.com/fotw/flags/ba-rs.html Flag of Republika Srpska - FOTW.net]</ref>
While the Constitutional Court of Bosnia and Herzegovina declared the [[coat of arms of Republika Srpska]] unconstitutional, claiming that it did not represent the non-Serb ethnicities living in the entity, the flag was deemed to be in line with the [[Constitution of Bosnia and Herzegovina|constitution]]. The court ruled that though the combination of the colours relates to the [[Flag of Serbia|Serbian tricolor]], the use of red, blue and white are considered to be [[pan-Slavic colors|pan-Slavic colours]] as well.
==Gallery== <center> <gallery> File:Flag of the President of Republika Srpska.svg|Standard of the President File:Standard of the President of Republika Srpska (1995-2007).svg|Standard of the President (1995–2007) File:Standard of the Prime Minister of Republika Srpska (1995-2007).svg|Standard of the Prime Minister (1995–2007) File:Standard of the President of the People's Assembly of Srpska (1995-2007).svg|Standard of the President of the National Assembly (1995–2007) File:Standard of the Minister of Defence of Republika Srpska (1995–2007).svg|Standard of the Minister of Defence (1995–2007) </gallery> </center>
==Related flags== {{refimprove section|date=January 2017}} {{See also|List of Serbian flags|Flag of Serbia}} [[File:Unofficial Flag of Republika Srpska.png|thumb|Flag similar to the flag of the [[Serbian Orthodox Church]] which is often used by [[Bosnian Serbs]]]]The Serbian [[tricolor (flag)|tricolor]] has been used as the basis for other flags, most notably as [[Serbia]]'s official flag. [[Montenegro]] has also used the Serbian tricolor with varying shades of blue. Under [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|communist Yugoslavia]], the republics of Serbia and Montenegro had flags of same design and colors. Montenegro changed its flag in 1993 by altering the proportion and shade of blue in its flag and used this flag until 2004.
The Serbian tricolor was also the basis for the [[Republic of Serbian Krajina]]. The Serbian tricolor defaced with a [[Serbian cross]] is used as the flag of the [[Serbian Orthodox Church]].
