In [[Irish mythology]] '''Fodbgen''' or '''Odbgen''' (modern spelling: '''Foidhbhgen''' - "the despoiler") son of [[Sengann mac Dela|Sengann]] of the [[Fir Bolg]] became [[High King of Ireland]] when he overthrew his cousin [[Rinnal]] son of [[Genann]]. It is said that before his time there were no knots ([[Old Irish]] ''odb'') in trees.

He ruled for four years until he was overthrown by [[Eochaid mac Eirc]], Rinnal's grandson.

