{| class="infobox bordered" style="width: 25em; text-align: left; font-size: 95%;" |+ style="font-size: larger;" | '''GISCorps''' |- | colspan="2" style="text-align:center;" | [[Image:GISCorps.png|300px|]] |- ! Type: | [[Geographic information system]] services |- ! Country: | [[United States]] |- ! Chair: | Dianne Haley |- ! Launched: | October 2003 |- ! Website: | [http://www.giscorps.org/ GISCorps.org] |- |}
'''GISCorps''', founded in 2003, is a program initiated by the [[Urban and Regional Information Systems Association]] (URISA) that offers volunteer [[geographic information system|GIS]] services to under-served developing communities worldwide.
This volunteer based organization is headed by a team of professionals trained in urban and regional development. GISCorps has approximately 1,000 volunteers located in five continents and prepared to work on both domestic and international projects. Their services are used for supplementing humanitarian relief, enhancing environmental analysis and fostering economic as well as community development. They promote the use of information technology for more accurate and efficient means of illustrating and improving the civic infrastructure of a region.
== Projects == GISCorps has assisted in the following projects:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.giscorps.org/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=22&Itemid=2|title=GISCorps - Our Projects|last=Administrator|website=www.giscorps.org|access-date=2017-04-16}}</ref> * Filtering Data for [[Hurricane Matthew]] in 2016 * Data Collection in Burundi * Mission with [[World Food Programme]] in North Korea during 2016 * Geocoding Locations in Niger
== See also == * [http://www.earthwatch.org/ Earthwatch Institute – United States] * [http://www.spatiallink.org/ SpatialLink.org] – Linking Spatial Professionals and Volunteers Through Search, Profile, News, Blog, Forum, Map, Chat, WIKI, WAP and Other GIS Tools * [http://www.scgis.org/ The Society for Conservation GIS]
