The following are the Junior world records in [[Olympic weightlifting]]. They are the best results set in competition by athletes aged 15 to 20 throughout the entire calendar year of the performance. Records are maintained in each [[weight class]] for the [[snatch (weightlifting)|snatch]], [[Clean and jerk]], and total for both lifts by the [[International Weightlifting Federation]].
The recognition of the Junior classification and subsequent record keeping began in 1962 for men and 1995 for women. The first stand-alone Junior World Championships were held in 1975 for men and 1995 for women.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120128092103/http://ogv.asn.or.at/infos.htm Gottfried Schödl: ''Historisches Kalendarium''] {{de icon}}</ref>
