{{other uses|RTL (disambiguation){{!}}RTL|Radio Luxembourg (disambiguation){{!}}Radio Luxemburg}} {{coord|49|38|13.23|N|6|09|50.15|E|display=title}}
{{Unreferenced|date=April 2012}}
[[File:RTL-RADIO-Deutschlands-Hitradio.png|thumb|Station logo]] '''RTL Radio''' is a German commercial radio station based in [[Berlin]] and the part of the [[RTL Group]]. It originated as the German language service of [[Radio Luxembourg]], which began broadcasting after [[World War II]] from [[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg|Luxembourg]]. It broadcasts [[adult contemporary music]] nationally via cable, satellite and internet and regionally via [[FM broadcasting|FM]] in Luxembourg, [[Rheinland-Pfalz]], [[Saarland]], eastern [[Belgium]], and [[Lorraine]].
==History== [[File:EU_location_LUX.png|thumb|right|250px|Location of Luxembourg (circled).]] RTL Radio began broadcasting as the German service of Radio Luxembourg on 15 July 1957. Along with the Saarland-based pirate radio Europe 1, Luxembourg interfered with the non-commercial monopoly imposed by the German states since broadcasting first started in the country. Apart from advertising reaching German radios for the first time, RTL also introduced Germans from both East and West to rock-and-roll music which contrasted to the classical repertoire that dominated mainland services.
In 1990, Radio Luxembourg was renamed RTL Hörfunk. On 1 July 2015 RTL Radio branded itself ''RTL Radio – Deutschlands Hit-Radio'' and moved its studios from the [[City of Luxembourg]] to [[Berlin]].
RTL Radio has slots on analog and digital cable, and transmits digital signals via the [[Astra (satellite)|Astra]] 1L satellites.
== External links == * [http://rtlradio.de/ Homepage of RTL Radio] (''in German'') * [http://www.rtlradio.lu/ Homepage of RTL Radio for Luxembourg] (''in German'') * [http://www.radiotreff.de/rtl/ History of the German service of Radio Luxemburg] (''in German'')
